sage.model.loader.ogreXML

Class OgreXMLParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • sage.model.loader.SAGEXMLParser
      • sage.model.loader.ogreXML.OgreXMLParser

  • public class OgreXMLParser
extends SAGEXMLParser
    OgreXMLParser is used to parse OgreXML files containing geometry, material, and animation data and turn them into a Group of Model3DTriMeshes to be rendered.

    Clients construct an instance of OgreXMLParser and invoke loadModel(String, String, String), passing Strings giving file names containing the mesh, material, and animation XML data files; the method returns a Group containing the Model3DTriMeshes defined in the XML files.

    By default loadModel(String, String, String) silently ignores unrecognized XML elements in the input file; printing of warning messages can be enabled by setting the verbose flag false (see sage.model.loader.ogreXML).

    Author:
    Morgan Darke
